Walk through the math required to derive two quantities \varepsilon and \lambda. I believe there may be a missing spatial dependence to make the initial condition hold. Specifically, the sentence:

> The initial coarse-graining scale \(\varepsilon_0\) has a unique value which must be chosen to satisfy the initial condition \(\mathrm{j}_f(x,0,\varepsilon_0) = n\). 

can't be entirely correct. Furthermore, the section deriving big O for all the quantities related to dimension reduction is unfinished.

Your task in one sentence:
Rigorously derive the parameters \varepsilon and \lambda and show that the scaling laws in terms of \lambda are all correct.

Manuscript in question:
